UY TICKETS','How to Purchase Disabled Tickets','<h3>How to Purchase Disabled Tickets</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Disabled Supporter Ticket Application Process</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Members</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Members can make an application for their ticket by completing the disabled supporter home/away ticket application form which can be downloaded here. Supporters need to complete the form and submit via email to access@chelseafc.com during the relevant sales period as advertised.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Once the application has been accepted, the supporter will receive an email advising them to log into their online ticketing account here to pay for their ticket.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Supporters log into their account by using their membership number and password. If you have not set a password, you can log in by using your date of birth in the 8-digit format DDMMYYYY.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If this does not work, you can request a password reset by clicking the button. Please ensure the email address on your account is a valid email address.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The personal assistant ticket will be process by the Access team once payment has been received for your main ticket.&nbsp; Disabled members MUST NOT purchase tickets for matches online as you will not receive a personal assistant ticket.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Season Ticket Holders - Home Matches</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Season ticket holders who purchase their ticket for additional home matches can do so by logging into their online ticketing account here.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Supporters can log into their account by using their season ticket number and password, if you have not set a password, you can log in by using your date of birth in the 8 digit format DD/MM/YYYY.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If this does not work, you can request a password reset by clicking the button. Please ensure the email address on your account is a valid email address.